Git diff doesn't detect untracked files. When checking for changes after copying new files into a git repo, you must `git add -A` first, then check `git diff --staged --quiet`. The pattern `git diff --quiet && git diff --staged --quiet` only sees tracked/staged changes, not new untracked files.